            <character>Lord Henry</character>
            <speech>All right, Uncle George, I’ll tell her, but it won’t have any effect. Philanthropic people lose all sense of humanity. It is their distinguishing characteristic.</speech>
        </dialogue>
    </paragraph>
    <paragraph>
        <description>The old gentleman growled approvingly and rang the bell for his servant. Lord Henry passed up the low arcade into Burlington Street and turned his steps in the direction of Berkeley Square.</description>
    </paragraph>
